# Vercel Web Analytics Installation Report

## Summary
Vercel Web Analytics was **already installed and properly configured** in this project. No code changes were required.

## Current Configuration

### Package Installation ✅
- `@vercel/analytics` version 2.0.1 is installed in package.json
- Dependencies have been installed via npm

### Implementation ✅
- **File**: `web/src/app/layout.tsx`
- **Import**: `import { Analytics } from "@vercel/analytics/next";`
- **Component**: `<Analytics />` placed correctly in the root layout's `<body>` tag

### Framework
- **Next.js App Router** (v16.2.3)
- Implementation follows the official Vercel documentation for Next.js App Router

## Verification Steps Completed

1. ✅ **Fetched latest documentation** from https://vercel.com/docs/analytics/quickstart
2. ✅ **Identified framework**: Next.js with App Router
3. ✅ **Verified installation**: @vercel/analytics@2.0.1 is present in package.json
4. ✅ **Verified configuration**: Analytics component correctly added to layout.tsx
5. ✅ **Installed dependencies**: Ran `npm install` to ensure all packages are installed
6. ✅ **Build verification**: Successfully built the project with `npm run build`
7. ✅ **Updated lock file**: package-lock.json updated during dependency installation

## Implementation Details

The Analytics component is correctly placed according to the official documentation:

```typescript
export default function RootLayout({ children }: { children: React.ReactNode }) {
  return (
    <html lang="en">
      <body>
        {children}
        <Analytics />  // ← Vercel Analytics component
      </body>
    </html>
  );
}
```

This placement ensures analytics tracking is active across all pages in the application.

## Next Steps

To complete the setup on Vercel:
1. Deploy the application to Vercel (if not already deployed)
2. Enable Web Analytics in the Vercel Dashboard (Analytics tab)
3. Verify analytics data collection by checking the dashboard after deployment

